<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1196&amp;p=14063#p14063"><![CDATA[
It's set up to work with carts from the rest of the world, just a matter of someone having them and a copynes. I'll be getting another big batch of all new (to DB) US carts soon, which will bring it a lot closer to a complete US set.<br /><br />It is along the lines of NSRT, with much more extensive info and less "crap". I don't think it will replace GoodNES anymore than NSRT replacing GoodSNES, more of a user preference. In fact, I have been in close contact with Cowering ever since I started this project and have been sharing this data with him. The next GoodNES release will have a lot of [!] in it and corrected headers.<br /><br />On a side note, I finally got to working on a guide for the software, I may possibly have it up by the end of the day.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=158">BootGod</a> — Sun Jun 11, 2006 10:08 am</p><hr />
