<title type="html"><![CDATA[Nes Cart DB site / CopyNES software]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1196&amp;p=13847#p13847"><![CDATA[
CRC32 and MD5 are near useless for file identification nowadays; stick with SHA-1 for now. (SHA-1 is Nintendo approved, as it's used by the Nintendo DS firmware to verify digital signatures on DS Download Play binaries.)<br /><br />Yes, it would probably be best to go back to the original dumps and SHA-1 them. In fact, it might be better to SHA-1 each 16 KB PRG ROM segment and each 8 KB CHR ROM segment for easier early detection of hacked versions.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Mon Jun 05, 2006 6:31 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
